No more runs until the death threats die down,

374
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:50,790
这是新规则
that's the new rule.

375
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,460
但他们让你去办公室了
But they let you go to the office.

376
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:54,410
因为我坐的是防弹车
Because I was in a bulletproof car.

377
00:19:57,020 --> 00:19:59,940
那这样一来我们是没戒烟了吗
Does this mean we've officially not quit?

378
00:20:00,330 --> 00:20:02,320
我们向来不会轻言放弃  不是吗
We've never been quitters, have we?

379
00:20:04,150 --> 00:20:06,210
先生  安德伍德夫人
Sir, Mrs. Underwood,

380
00:20:06,380 --> 00:20:07,570
很抱歉打扰你们
sorry to interrupt.

381
00:20:08,190 --> 00:20:09,160
我要回家了
I was gonna head home,

382
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,100
但如果你们想让我留下  我就留下
but I'll stick around if you want me to.

383
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:13,980
不  你已经熬很久了  去睡会儿吧
Oh, no. You've been up long enough. Get some sleep.

384
00:20:14,540 --> 00:20:16,000
我明天一早就回来
I'll be back first thing in the morning.

385
00:20:16,010 --> 00:20:17,990
谢谢你今天照顾我
Thank you for looking after me today.

386
00:20:18,470 --> 00:20:19,560
我的荣幸  夫人
My pleasure, ma'am.

387
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:21,540
先生  安德伍德夫人  再见
Sir, Mrs. Underwood.

388
00:20:26,190 --> 00:20:27,540
他非常尽忠
He's very dedicated.

389
00:20:27,690 --> 00:20:28,840
确实
He is.

390
00:20:29,110 --> 00:20:31,180
很难找到艾德华这样的人
It's rare to find someone like Edward.

391
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:35,300
怎么了
What?

392
00:20:35,570 --> 00:20:37,270
你从不直呼他名字
You never use his first name.

393
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,370
是吗
Oh, did I?

394
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:45,520
我觉得这样谈论她不太好
I don't feel right talking about her like this.

395
00:20:46,050 --> 00:20:49,580
就是...严格讲  她现在是我上司
It's just... technically, she's my boss now.

396
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:50,970
有规矩的
There's a certain protocol.

397
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:52,780
这是道格的意思
This is coming directly from Doug.

398
00:20:52,780 --> 00:20:56,300
也就是副总统本人的意思
Which means it's coming directly from the vice president.

399
00:21:02,890 --> 00:21:05,670
我见到过几次丹顿先生
I have seen Mr. Danton around from time to time.

400
00:21:06,570 --> 00:21:08,640
你知道他跟议员女士在商讨什么吗
Do you know what he and the congresswoman were discussing?

401
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,030
不知道  都是私人会面
No, they were private meetings.

402
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:13,010
你有预约日程表吗
Do you have the appointment schedule?

403
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:14,770
我想看看日期
I'd like to look at the dates.

404
00:21:15,390 --> 00:21:17,440
不是正式约会
These weren't formal appointments.

405
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:19,500
他就是顺路来看看
He just stops by.

406
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:22,050
大多数都是晚上很晚的时候
Most of the time pretty late at night.

407
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:26,230
钱是不是从中国来的
Did the money originate in China?

408
00:21:26,730 --> 00:21:28,820
钱来自部落收入
The money came from tribal revenue.

409
00:21:29,110 --> 00:21:31,830
我们的联邦选举委员会报告上写得很清楚
As our FEC reports clearly stated.

410
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:32,620
我换个说法
Let me rephrase.

411
00:21:32,620 --> 00:21:34,270
这些部落收入是否来自
Did any of that revenue come from

412
00:21:34,270 --> 00:21:36,780
去你赌场的中国游客
Chinese visitors who gambled at your casino?

413
00:21:36,790 --> 00:21:38,820
我们有来自世界各地的游客
We have visitors from all over the world.

414
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:42,190
我只关注一个叫冯山德的商人
I'm speaking specifically about a businessman named Xander Feng.

415
00:21:43,810 --> 00:21:45,370
我不知道那是谁
I have no idea who that is.

416
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:47,560
我查到空管局的记录显示
I'm looking at FAA flight records that show

417
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:50,630
他名下的一架私人飞机曾多次飞抵堪萨斯城
a private plane he owns making numerous trips to Kansas City.

418
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:53,160
我问过密苏里巴士豪车
And I spoke with Missouri Bus and Limo,

419
00:21:53,310 --> 00:21:55,940
他们负责把中国游客接到你的赌场
which has transported Chinese visitors to your casino.

420
00:21:55,940 --> 00:21:56,710
赛义德女士
Ms. Said--

421
00:21:56,710 --> 00:21:57,520
萨伊德
Sayyad.

422
00:21:57,520 --> 00:22:00,630
萨伊德女士  我回你的电话
Ms. Sayyad, the only reason I returned your call

423
00:22:00,630 --> 00:22:02,570
只是因为你在《电讯报》工作
was because you work for The Telegraph.

424
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:06,040
我不是每天都能接受你们这种大报的采访
It's not every day that I get a call from a paper as big as yours.

425
00:22:06,260 --> 00:22:07,990
但我不明白你究竟想问什么
But I don't know what you're trying to get at here,

426
00:22:07,990 --> 00:22:08,970
所以如果你不介意
so if you'll excuse--

427
00:22:08,970 --> 00:22:10,350
那雷蒙德·塔斯克呢
What about Raymond Tusk?

428
00:22:12,250 --> 00:22:13,220
他怎么了
What about him?

429
00:22:13,430 --> 00:22:14,800
冯和塔斯克有关系
Feng has ties to Tusk.

430
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,340
塔斯克与总统有关系
Tusk has ties to the president.

431
00:22:16,340 --> 00:22:17,650
你与冯有关系
You have ties to Feng.

432
00:22:17,650 --> 00:22:20,290
这看起来像是外国资金被用来左右政治...
That looks like foreign money being used to influence political--

433
00:22:20,290 --> 00:22:23,460
你所暗示的事不仅失实
What you're insinuating is not only wrong,

434
00:22:23,740 --> 00:22:25,080
更是诽谤
it's libelous.

435
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:26,710
如果是真的就不是
Not if it's true.

436
00:22:26,750 --> 00:22:29,560
我会毫不犹豫地让我的律师介入
I won't bat an eyelash getting my attorneys involved.

437
00:22:30,280 --> 00:22:31,740
塔斯克也这么威胁我
Tusk made the same threat.

438
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:34,580
如果一个身家四百亿的人吓不倒我
If a man worth $40 billion doesn't intimidate me,

439
00:22:34,590 --> 00:22:36,400
你也吓不倒我  拉...
you certainly don't, Mr. Lan--

440
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:39,980
喂
Hello?

441
00:22:42,410 --> 00:22:43,520
他挂断了
He hung up.

442
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:45,940
我和这完全没关系  雷蒙德
I had nothing to do with it, Raymond.

443
00:22:46,430 --> 00:22:49,020
我在电话这头都闻得到谎言的臭气
I can smell the horseshit through the phone.

444
00:22:49,020 --> 00:22:51,150
你觉得我会冒这么大的险吗
You think I'd put myself at this great a risk?

445
00:22:51,450 --> 00:22:53,690
兔子急了都咬人
Desperate men are capable of anything.

446
00:22:53,820 --> 00:22:56,080
我和你一样希望事情平息
I want it to go away just like you do.

447
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:57,810
那就让她停手
Then pull her back.

448
00:22:57,970 --> 00:22:59,940
我控制不了媒体  雷蒙德
I have no control over the press, Raymond.

449
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:02,100
你只会害了你自己  不是我  弗兰克
You'll destroy yourself, Frank, not me.

450
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:04,400
多谢你多余的忠告
Thank you for that unsolicited advice.

451
00:23:05,590 --> 00:23:06,430
和道尔一起
Work with Doyle,

452
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:07,810
确保我们没有弱点
make sure we have no weak spots.

453
00:23:07,810 --> 00:23:08,530
我这就打电话给他
I'll call him now.

454
00:23:08,550 --> 00:23:09,710
南茜怎么说
What did Nancy say?

455
00:23:10,090 --> 00:23:14,460
看来杰姬可能和敌人上床了
Well, it looks like Jackie may be sleeping with the enemy.

456
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:19,570
拉尼根说我们有诽谤的风险没说错
Lanagin is correct in saying we run the risk of libel.

457
00:23:19,570 --> 00:23:21,180
他们之间的联系是有事实依据的
These links are supported by fact.

458
00:23:21,180 --> 00:23:23,170
都是单线  你不能连成圈
Individually, but you can't complete the circle.

459
00:23:23,170 --> 00:23:24,650
我不是说我们要大标题写
I'm not saying the headline should read:

460
00:23:24,650 --> 00:23:27,550
"洗钱黑幕揭秘"  加大惊叹号
Money Laundering Scheme Exposed! Exclamation point.

461
00:23:27,550 --> 00:23:30,300
只是把我们已知的情况原样呈现
Just that we present the landscape as we currently know it.

462
00:23:30,330 --> 00:23:32,130
我们主要是一家财经报纸
We're first and foremost a financial paper.

463
00:23:32,130 --> 00:23:34,000
很多读者都崇拜雷蒙德·塔斯克
Many of our readers worship Raymond Tusk.

464
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,380
那我们就该保护他吗
So we just protect him?

465
00:23:35,380 --> 00:23:37,800
我们不能暗示我们无法证实的联系
We don't insinuate connections we can't back up.

466
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:39,370
有任何诉讼的机会
If there's any basis for litigation,

467
00:23:39,370 --> 00:23:41,240
他的团队肯定不会放过
you can be sure his team will be aggressive.

468
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:42,900
他们以前也曾让报社破产
They've bankrupted papers before.

469
00:23:42,910 --> 00:23:45,170
我觉得你应该慢慢来
I think you should slow down and take your time.

470
00:23:45,210 --> 00:23:46,450
什么时候你有了完整的故事
When, and if, you have a story--

471
00:23:46,450 --> 00:23:47,590
马克斯菲尔德先生
Mr. Maxfield,

472
00:23:48,030 --> 00:23:49,440
雷蒙德·塔斯克打电话过来
Raymond Tusk is on the line.

473
00:23:50,150 --> 00:23:51,420
你给他打电话了吗
Did you put in a call to him?

474
00:23:51,470 --> 00:23:52,370
昨天
Yesterday.

475
00:23:52,370 --> 00:23:53,980
他指名要找你  先生
He's specifically asking for you, sir.

476
00:23:53,980 --> 00:23:56,350
我们和拉尼根通话还不到半小时
We got off the phone with Lanagin less than 30 minutes ago.

477
00:23:56,360 --> 00:23:58,680
说明拉尼根立刻打电话给塔斯克了
That means that Tusk was the first call Lanagin made.

478
00:23:58,950 --> 00:24:00,220
告诉他我会打回去
Tell him I'll return.

479
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:01,590
你联系过白宫了吗
Did you reach out to the White House?

480
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:03,590
他们在明天总统的新闻发布会前
They're not talking to anyone until after the president

481
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:05,070
不接受任何采访
does his press briefing tomorrow.

482
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:06,420
好吧
All right.

483
00:24:06,420 --> 00:24:08,660
把事情再详细给我说一遍
Walk me through all of this again, point by point.

484
00:25:03,350 --> 00:25:04,190
密查姆
Meechum.

485
00:25:04,420 --> 00:25:05,850
我们明天再说  先生
We can talk tomorrow, sir.

486
00:25:06,970 --> 00:25:09,290
不用  怎么了
No. What is it?

487
00:25:16,150 --> 00:25:19,750
我想申请全职做您妻子的安保人员
I'd like to put in a request to be on your wife's detail full-time.

488
00:25:20,070 --> 00:25:22,320
直到死亡威胁消失
At least until the death threats quiet down.

489
00:25:23,020 --> 00:25:24,570
这很体贴
That's very thoughtful.

490
00:25:24,630 --> 00:25:26,490
您不同意我是不会去的  先生
I'll only do it if you approve, sir.

491
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:27,670
你和克莱尔谈过了吗
Have you spoken to Claire?

492
00:25:27,670 --> 00:25:29,870
她回来的时候说过了  她觉得不错
When she came home. She likes the idea.

493
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:31,520
那就这样做吧
Then I think we should do it.

494
00:25:31,790 --> 00:25:33,250
我去告诉洛克兰探员
I'll let Agent Rockland know.

495
00:25:36,180 --> 00:25:37,490
抱歉打扰  先生
Sorry for interrupting you, sir.

496
00:25:37,530 --> 00:25:39,060
你没打扰什么
You didn't interrupt anything.

497
00:25:39,550 --> 00:25:40,540
晚安  先生
Good night, sir.

498
00:25:40,590 --> 00:25:41,620
晚安  密查姆
Good night, Meechum.

499
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:51,010
你肯定猜不到刚才发生了什么
You'll never believe what just happened.

500
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:52,230
什么
What?

501
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,500
密查姆走进办公室
Meechum came into the office

502
00:25:54,500 --> 00:25:57,140
发现我看的东西
and found me watching something...

503
00:25:58,110 --> 00:25:59,850
不是新闻
...other than the news.

504
00:26:03,850 --> 00:26:05,320
不是吧
Oh, no.

505
00:26:05,540 --> 00:26:07,720
他很懂规矩
He was very professional about it.

506
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:11,050
-你有没有...  -没有  我只是看而已
- Were you...? - No, no, no. I was just watching.

507
00:26:11,610 --> 00:26:13,080
真是好笑
That's really funny.

508
00:26:14,420 --> 00:26:16,160
你呢  你在看什么
What about you? What are you watching?

509
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:17,990
康纳给我的视频
The video Connor gave me.

510
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,800
我们第一次竞选州参议员
It's our first state senate race.

511
00:26:19,830 --> 00:26:21,240
我都忘干净了
I forgot about that.

512
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:23,720
我也是  今早在桌上看到才想起来
So did I, until I found it in the desk this morning.

513
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:24,710
让我看看
Let me see.

514
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:27,560
...经历过  就像我
...been there, like I have.

515
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:30,150
当然  有点德州味儿无伤大雅
Of course, it doesn't hurt to have a little Texas in them...

516
00:26:30,150 --> 00:26:33,650
-老天  我们当年多年轻  -是啊
- My God, look how young we are. - I know.

517
00:26:33,650 --> 00:26:36,490
大家都很和善  很热情
Everyone here has been so kind, and so welcoming.

518
00:26:36,490 --> 00:26:39,100
过不了多久她就要在克莱姆森扎根了
We'll have her rooting for Clemson before too long.

519
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:40,930
这我可做不到
That's where I have to draw the line.

520
00:26:45,820 --> 00:26:47,790
你怀念和亚当在一起的日子吗
Do you miss being with Adam?

521
00:26:48,290 --> 00:26:49,700
你怎么提起这个来
Where did that come from?

522
00:26:53,310 --> 00:26:54,550
怀念吗  不
Miss it? No.

523
00:26:55,110 --> 00:26:57,710
